            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.61.55-56_0001a" />

                <note type="curatorial">15 Aly Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Sep. 23, '70</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p> Yesterday Florence found a complete newspaper account of the 1917 commencement at the University of Neb. It gives all the names, including Willa Cather and myself as recipients of <del/> the Litt D degree.</p> <note type="authorial">(See inside)</note>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.61.55-56_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>    
                    
                <p>I still wonder why you rejected my testimony.</p>
                
                <p>There must be several more accounts &#8212; one in World-Herald of Omaha for certain.</p>
                
                <p>I received the <hi rend="double underline"><hi rend="caps">LLD</hi></hi> from <del>Creight</del>Creighton University <hi rend="underline">in absentia</hi> while I was on the Post-Dispatch in 1928.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With affection</salute>
                
                    <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">55</fw>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.61.55-56_0002b"/>
                <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p><del>W</del>We were named <hi rend="underline">as present</hi> and receiving the same degree. An account is given of Theodore Roosevelt and General Pershing who were unable to be present and were awarded their degrees <hi rend="underline">in absentia</hi>.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>J. N.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
